title: Understanding Column Elements
text: Columns in a dataset are often labeled with names that describe the type of data they contain. These names help users understand what kind of information is stored in each column.

title: Choosing a Descriptive Name
text: When naming a column, it's important to choose a name that clearly describes the data it contains. This helps in understanding and analyzing the data effectively.

title: Identifying the Correct Column Name
text: Consider the options provided: Start date, thing1, X, Info. Which one best describes a column that contains dates when something begins?
